My suggestion for dialogue is to read it out loud. I understand that in this sphere, a lot of us don't really have the option of asking for a proofreader, so just sort of talk to yourself through it.
As for the rest of it, any text editing program on the computer can solve the grammar issue, but things like whether or not the chick is his sister needs to be sorted first for the story to be coherent.
If you really want to write, then keep at it. I'll be honest, this work is the sort of thing me and my buddies pass around and read in silly voices to make fun of fanfiction, but if you genuinely want to tell stories, you need to write more. I would suggest not sharing many of your first works with the world, but definitely get some practice. Take your works, and watch some YouTube videos about the do's and don'ts of writing. When you think you have something pretty decent, share it with the thread and/or a writing community, and ask for criticism. From there, you will git gud.
